  "prompt": "If you were born deaf, what language would you think in?",
  "response": "If someone is born deaf, their internal thought process would likely develop using visual language, such as sign language, or conceptual/imagistic thinking. Since language is learned through experience, a person who has never heard spoken language would not have an \"inner voice\" in the same auditory way hearing people do. Their thoughts would be more visual, spatial, and based on the language they learn\u2014typically sign language. The brain is remarkably adaptable and will create language processing mechanisms using the available sensory input.",
